did.abstract: This collection contains records created by the International Brotherhood of Teamsters Local 544. Included are correspondence, meeting minutes and agendas, working agreements and drafts, personnel and grievance records, handbooks, constitutions, by-laws, rosters, ledgers, brochures and pamphlets, photographs, and ephemera. The material dates from 1930-2013.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Local 544 of the International Brotherhood of Teamsters is located in Minnesota. It was chartered in 1936. The leaders of 544 went on to develop the area and conference bargaining that exists today in the International Brotherhood of Teamsters. It has merged with other Locals throughout the years, including Local 120 in 1998.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into 5 series: Working Agreements and Related Correspondence; Grievance Records; Company Records; Teamster Records; Ephemera.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. Series 2, subseries 2 is restricted for 25 years from date of creation. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains correspondence, meeting minutes and agendas, working agreements and drafts, personnel and grievance records, handbooks, constitutions, by-laws, rosters, ledgers, brochures and pamphlets, photographs, and ephemera. The material dates from 1930-2013. These are the records of International Brotherhood of Teamsters Local 544, located in Minnesota.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials of this series include finalized working agreements, drafts, and related correspondence. They range in date from 1952-2013. These materials represent the negotiations and end results of developing working agreements between various companies and the Teamsters.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Folders in this series are arranged alphabetically by the name of the company.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This series is divided into two subseries for grievance committee agendas and minutes and individual company records. Folder titles are arranged alphabetically by committee or company.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials of this series include the agendas and minutes for different grievance committees, with the bulk coming from the Minnesota Joint State Grievance Committee, Minnesota/South Dakota Joint State Grievance Committee, and Wisconsin Joint Auto Transport Committee. Grievance records and associated correspondence from individual companies are also included in this series. They range in date from 1963-2009. These materials document the proceedings and decisions of grievance hearings and the individual complaints.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This series is divided into four subseries: Conference and Meeting Minutes and Agendas; By-Laws, Constitutions, and Rosters; Miscellaneous Publications, Correspondence, and Memos; Ledgers. Folders are arranged alphabetically by title. Folder titles for the third subseries were retained as much as possible. Ledgers are arranged by size and by date when possible.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials of this series include conference/meeting minutes and agendas, union by-laws, constitutions, ritual booklets, rosters, pension and health plans, ledgers, and miscellaneous publications, correspondence, and memoranda. The bulk of the meeting minutes and agendas are from the Central States Joint Area Committee and National Automobile Transporters. The majority of the ledgers are from Local 387. These materials range in date from 1930-2006.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The patches, stickers, and photographs are grouped by similar items and put in folders, which are alphabetically arranged. The other objects are grouped and stored according to like objects.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials of this series include cassettes and VHS tapes, patches, stickers, photographs, t-shirts, hats, banners and posters, and a notary press. The materials of this series are from Locals 387, 487, and 544. These materials range in date from 1937-2001, though many of the items are undated.
